WEBVTT

00:33.892 --> 00:34.894
♪ Hey ♪

00:35.989 --> 00:37.594
♪ Here she comes now ♪

00:40.707 --> 00:42.741
♪ Oh, you know her ♪

00:42.766 --> 00:44.703
♪ Would you look at that hair ♪

00:44.728 --> 00:46.683
♪ Yeah, you know her ♪

00:47.005 --> 00:48.761
♪ Check out those shoes ♪

00:48.786 --> 00:50.848
♪ She looks like
She stepped out of ♪

00:50.873 --> 00:53.809
♪ The middle
Of somebody's blues ♪

00:56.289 --> 00:57.964
♪ She looks like
The Sunday comics ♪

00:57.989 --> 00:59.004
Linda.

01:00.219 --> 01:01.421
♪ She thinks she's-- ♪

01:01.446 --> 01:02.572
Earth to Linda.

01:04.788 --> 01:05.853
Oh.

01:08.328 --> 01:09.604
Still working
on the company report?

01:09.629 --> 01:11.689
Uh, I finished that last week.

01:11.784 --> 01:14.442
I was just working on
some projections for next month.

01:14.687 --> 01:15.941
You include
last year's numbers?

01:15.966 --> 01:17.284
Mm-hmm.
All index-correlated

01:17.315 --> 01:19.623
with next year's
estimated quarterlies included.

01:20.613 --> 01:22.871
- You're amazing.
- Oh.

01:23.088 --> 01:24.891
God, I have so much trouble
with this stuff.

01:25.290 --> 01:27.359
All right. They're all waiting.

01:27.384 --> 01:30.021
Showtime. I'm right behind ya.

01:30.105 --> 01:31.806
-Oh.
-Oh.

01:31.831 --> 01:33.604
No, they shrunk it down
to a smaller group.

01:34.086 --> 01:36.726
I'm actually just,
uh, dropping it off.

01:39.499 --> 01:41.785
I-I put the numbers together.

01:42.195 --> 01:43.584
They told me they wanted me
in the room

01:43.609 --> 01:44.955
in case there were
any questions.

01:44.998 --> 01:47.099
Questions.
Yeah, I don't really know.

01:47.694 --> 01:50.618
I mean, you know how it's been
around here lately, Linda,

01:50.643 --> 01:51.677
it's just all...

01:52.010 --> 01:53.112
...up in the air.

01:54.994 --> 01:56.051
Yeah.

01:56.076 --> 01:58.712
But don't worry. They'll know
who did the heavy lifting.

01:58.897 --> 02:01.132
Your name is right on top.

02:03.502 --> 02:04.535
Okay.

02:05.396 --> 02:06.932
-Okay.
-Thanks.

02:07.373 --> 02:08.407
Good luck in there.

02:11.723 --> 02:12.723
Well...

02:13.312 --> 02:15.909
Guess that old
elevator to success

02:15.934 --> 02:17.734
is out of order again, huh?

02:18.697 --> 02:20.671
- What?
- Oh.

02:20.696 --> 02:23.795
I was just saying, we're gonna
have to keep taking the stairs.

02:24.216 --> 02:26.332
One step at a time.

02:27.931 --> 02:29.022
Oi!

02:29.047 --> 02:31.022
-Chase!
-Oh. Hey, what's up?

02:31.703 --> 02:33.295
-'Sup?
-Uh...

02:33.391 --> 02:35.876
A few of us after work
are hitting Milly and Al's for--

02:35.901 --> 02:36.973
-So down.
-Oh!

02:36.998 --> 02:40.697
Milly and--
That's the best karaoke in town.

02:40.899 --> 02:42.200
- Yeah, it is.
- Could really go for a song

02:42.225 --> 02:43.433
and a drink tonight.

02:43.903 --> 02:47.222
My go-to is
"One Way Or Another."

02:48.775 --> 02:49.810
Uh...

02:49.835 --> 02:50.777
- Is that...
- No?

02:50.802 --> 02:52.090
-No.
-Blondie?

02:52.183 --> 02:54.111
-Debbie Harry? Oh, man.
-No.

02:54.142 --> 02:54.910
- All right.
- All right.

02:54.935 --> 02:56.529
"I'm gonna get ya, get ya,
get ya, get ya."

02:56.554 --> 02:57.623
Hey!

02:57.648 --> 02:59.221
You gotta Google her.

02:59.605 --> 03:01.439
Um, do you have a go-to, or...

03:23.188 --> 03:25.790
Here is the company review
I prepared.

03:26.491 --> 03:29.082
Lost a lot of sleep putting
this little baby together.

03:29.107 --> 03:31.806
But no rest
for the wicked, am I right?

03:40.785 --> 03:43.288
So get this.
After all that work,

03:43.664 --> 03:44.944
I didn't even get to go
to the meeting.

03:46.015 --> 03:49.305
I swear, Sweetie, sometimes...

03:49.788 --> 03:51.991
Yeah, I'm still sitting
with the assistants.

03:52.016 --> 03:54.403
But, all that changes tomorrow.

03:54.587 --> 03:55.657
When Bradley--

03:56.303 --> 04:00.460
Mr. Preston officially
takes over for his father.

04:01.553 --> 04:04.229
Yep. His father said,
right in front of him,

04:04.254 --> 04:06.629
that I was next in line for VP.

04:06.705 --> 04:09.101
So, he knows my value
to the company.

04:10.596 --> 04:13.227
And he's good-looking,
and he's single

04:13.251 --> 04:15.509
and charming,
and blah, blah, blah.

04:15.533 --> 04:17.790
And I told you how flirty he was
with me at the Christmas party.

04:17.814 --> 04:18.815
Whoo!

04:19.904 --> 04:20.906
But...

04:21.466 --> 04:23.284
That has nothing to do
with anything.

04:25.271 --> 04:26.698
We just need to focus on...

04:27.814 --> 04:30.619
the new office, the new title...

04:33.386 --> 04:35.017
...maybe that bigger apartment.

04:39.611 --> 04:41.379
We're gonna
spread our wings a little.

04:43.469 --> 04:44.787
It's not over for us.

04:46.191 --> 04:47.449
Best is yet to come.

04:49.889 --> 04:51.228
Well, exactly.

04:53.493 --> 04:54.529
We deserve it.

05:01.600 --> 05:02.599
You deserve it.

05:04.268 --> 05:05.304
Hmm?

05:09.794 --> 05:11.307
Up you go. Come on.

05:17.405 --> 05:18.431
Mmm.

05:22.293 --> 05:23.492
We deserve it.

05:25.623 --> 05:26.662
Mmm!

05:26.799 --> 05:28.401
It's time. Okay.

05:31.290 --> 05:33.436
Who'll have
what it takes to outwit...

05:33.461 --> 05:34.855
-Outplay, outlast.
-...outplay, and outlast...

05:34.880 --> 05:36.040
all the rest.

05:36.100 --> 05:40.569
This is Survivor.

05:40.599 --> 05:43.544
If Kishan gets voted off
tonight, I swear to God.

05:46.073 --> 05:47.101
That's what I'm saying.

05:57.922 --> 06:00.099
Ladies and gentlemen, may
I have your attention please?

06:00.506 --> 06:04.137
I'd like to present to you your
new president, Bradley Preston.

06:09.101 --> 06:10.497
This is Marshall, IT...

06:10.522 --> 06:12.558
Marshall, look forward
to working with you.

06:12.583 --> 06:14.463
- Sonja. Sales.
- Nice to meet you, Mr. Preston.

06:14.523 --> 06:17.203
-Mmm.
-And finally, Sierra, Marketing.

06:17.228 --> 06:18.430
All right, sit down,
sit down, sit down.

06:18.455 --> 06:19.723
Okay, everybody back to work.

06:20.713 --> 06:22.645
Got a few things to talk to you
about in the office, okay?

06:22.670 --> 06:23.543
Sure.

06:23.568 --> 06:24.755
Soon as we can,
we gotta get you--

06:24.780 --> 06:25.927
-Mr. Preston!
-Hi!

06:26.626 --> 06:28.296
Call me Bradley.
Nice to meet you.

06:28.501 --> 06:30.231
Oh, um...

06:30.402 --> 06:34.019
Linda Liddle.
We spoke at the Christmas party.

06:34.599 --> 06:36.201
-Um...
-Oh. That's right.

06:36.226 --> 06:37.765
No, yes. Of course.

06:37.790 --> 06:39.224
Of course,
it's great to see you again.

06:39.250 --> 06:41.724
Yes. You, too. And I'm so sorry
about your father.

06:41.749 --> 06:44.453
-I appreciate that.
-He was a very admirable man.

06:44.478 --> 06:45.520
He really
took me under his wing.

06:45.545 --> 06:47.080
-Yes. Me, too.
-Um...

06:47.285 --> 06:51.483
But I am so excited about this
opportunity to help you execute

06:51.508 --> 06:52.821
...your strategic vision

06:52.846 --> 06:55.555
and lead this company
into a new era of, um...

06:56.594 --> 06:57.814
Um...

06:59.419 --> 07:00.457
Era of success.

07:01.487 --> 07:03.756
-Exactly.
-Well, I hope to do just that.

07:03.816 --> 07:04.902
It's gonna be
a lot of work though.

07:04.927 --> 07:06.124
Big shoes to fill, right?

07:06.979 --> 07:08.291
Gonna need
all the help I can get.

07:10.394 --> 07:13.100
Well, and I have
the right shoes already.

07:13.140 --> 07:14.585
What's that?

07:15.006 --> 07:18.191
I call these my Liddle Mules.

07:18.291 --> 07:20.784
Had these girls a long time.
A lot of miles on them.

07:20.838 --> 07:24.342
And they can carry any load
you throw their way.

07:24.504 --> 07:26.038
-Yeah. I gotta get to it.
-Okay.

07:26.063 --> 07:27.110
Okay.

07:27.135 --> 07:28.569
Oh, my gosh. Look at your shoes.

07:28.594 --> 07:31.599
Those are fancy-pants.

07:31.690 --> 07:34.158
Just don't step
in any puddles, right?

07:34.393 --> 07:35.728
I'm sorry, I didn't catch that.

07:36.481 --> 07:38.104
Don't step in any puddles.

07:39.697 --> 07:41.326
-I'll try to avoid that.
-Okay.

07:42.202 --> 07:44.447
All right. Get back to work.

07:46.492 --> 07:48.512
All right, gentlemen. Let's get
our P's and Q's in order.

07:48.902 --> 07:51.117
Barbara, lovely to see you.
Can you hold my calls?

07:53.705 --> 07:54.733
No, that went well.

07:55.093 --> 07:56.163
You just wanna go with

07:56.188 --> 07:58.515
the, uh, consulting firm's
recommendations?

07:59.590 --> 08:00.641
That's funny, right?

08:00.666 --> 08:02.997
A consulting firm
hiring a consulting firm.

08:03.022 --> 08:04.617
-What is that?
-What?

08:04.702 --> 08:05.604
This.

08:06.003 --> 08:07.004
I don't know.

08:07.893 --> 08:08.896
-Smell it.
-No.

08:08.980 --> 08:10.248
-Yes.
-No.

08:10.273 --> 08:11.281
Yes.

08:19.205 --> 08:20.240
Smell it.

08:25.911 --> 08:26.915
Tuna fish.

08:28.093 --> 08:29.260
Tuna fish.

08:31.591 --> 08:32.988
It's that disgusting woman.

08:33.312 --> 08:36.213
The one who accosted me
with Payless orthopedics.

08:36.238 --> 08:39.110
Linda Liddle. Your father
promised her a promotion.

08:39.277 --> 08:41.364
-From manager to vice president.
-Did he?

08:41.486 --> 08:43.304
A big bump in title and salary.

08:43.528 --> 08:44.796
-Yeah.
-She's been waiting for it.

08:44.821 --> 08:46.802
Right. Well.
Donovan's getting that job.

08:47.894 --> 08:50.791
Your father relied on Linda.
Real workhorse.

08:50.883 --> 08:52.284
I dump everything on her.

08:52.343 --> 08:53.779
Does it look like I give a shit?

08:53.899 --> 08:55.256
It doesn't, right?
'Cause I don't.

08:55.487 --> 08:57.811
My father's not here anymore.
It's Donovan's.

08:58.777 --> 09:00.756
Plus, I already told them.
And move her.

09:00.781 --> 09:02.250
Satellite office, maybe.

09:02.281 --> 09:04.883
Somewhere far.
She makes me sick.

09:07.271 --> 09:08.806
We have Bangkok coming up.

09:09.328 --> 09:11.603
And we haven't even
cracked Appendix-D.

09:11.910 --> 09:13.911
Donovan will drown on his own.

09:14.393 --> 09:15.817
The whole thing could fall apart
without her.

09:15.842 --> 09:17.376
Okay. Fine.

09:17.897 --> 09:19.010
Bring her.

09:19.690 --> 09:21.762
She'll get Don-O up to speed.
And then we'll ship her out.

09:30.682 --> 09:32.604
Wait, wait, wait,
this is funny...

09:34.387 --> 09:35.549
That little shake...

09:36.500 --> 09:37.794
Whoop.

09:40.599 --> 09:42.119
All right. Ah.

09:42.801 --> 09:45.863
Gotta get back to work.

09:46.692 --> 09:49.789
All right. Back to work.

09:50.389 --> 09:52.852
Well, they seem kind of chummy.

09:52.877 --> 09:55.704
Well, yeah, he's being promoted
to vice president.

09:56.414 --> 09:58.324
Sorry. I'm sorry, what?

09:58.349 --> 10:00.086
Yeah, I'm typing
the company-wide email

10:00.111 --> 10:01.112
about it right now.

10:01.467 --> 10:03.601
-Oh, tell me you're kidding.
-Mm-mm-mm.

10:03.626 --> 10:06.087
I literally looked
at his LinkedIn profile,

10:06.112 --> 10:08.549
and they were in
the same frat in college.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.989
And they play golf together.
So, duh.

10:31.175 --> 10:32.381
Linda, what the heck?

10:32.884 --> 10:35.810
Uh, my final question would be,
how above and beyond

10:35.835 --> 10:37.902
would you be willing
to go for me?

10:37.927 --> 10:39.728
Yes?

10:39.792 --> 10:40.925
Mr. Preston?

10:41.186 --> 10:42.220
I'm in a meeting.

10:42.293 --> 10:44.321
I'm sorry. I just need
a moment of your time.

10:44.896 --> 10:46.065
-Right, well, I'm--
-Please.

10:47.607 --> 10:48.641
Please.

10:48.726 --> 10:49.730
Sure.

10:50.349 --> 10:51.404
We'll be in touch.

10:52.485 --> 10:54.327
Thanks for coming in.

10:56.300 --> 10:57.307
Sorry.

10:59.384 --> 11:00.764
Sorry to barge in like this--

11:00.788 --> 11:03.230
Nope. Open door policy.
What's up?

11:03.269 --> 11:05.724
Uh-- Well, I just heard
about the job--

11:05.749 --> 11:07.343
You're unhappy about
not getting the promotion.

11:08.114 --> 11:09.124
Well, yes.

11:09.386 --> 11:10.450
Yeah. Okay.

11:10.962 --> 11:13.186
Yes, respectfully, uh...

11:14.106 --> 11:16.041
Donovan has been here
for six months,

11:16.065 --> 11:18.523
and I have been here
for seven years, and-and--

11:19.410 --> 11:20.493
I hear you.

11:20.999 --> 11:23.947
Let's talk it out.
Come in, close the door.

11:24.608 --> 11:25.777
Let's talk about it.

11:28.320 --> 11:29.320
Hmm?

11:33.532 --> 11:34.693
Please, sit.

11:41.393 --> 11:44.630
Now, I'm going to be frank
with you. If that's all right.

11:45.291 --> 11:47.883
I know that you are great
with numbers.

11:48.392 --> 11:50.368
Kind of a savant.

11:50.416 --> 11:52.046
-Right?
-I am good with numbers, yes.

11:52.071 --> 11:54.272
Yes, and I've carefully
reviewed a lot of that work,

11:54.297 --> 11:57.278
and it is impressive,
so that's the positive.

11:57.303 --> 11:58.319
Thank you.

11:58.502 --> 12:00.426
But, I...

12:01.300 --> 12:03.468
...don't see you as being
somebody who's ready

12:03.493 --> 12:05.928
for an executive position
quite yet.

12:10.269 --> 12:11.312
Why?

12:11.476 --> 12:13.538
I guess, as a VP,
I would need somebody

12:13.563 --> 12:15.932
who is more of a people person.

12:16.687 --> 12:20.716
You know, somebody by my side
who is well-liked.

12:21.399 --> 12:22.702
Who can charm a room.

12:23.088 --> 12:25.191
Who can make a deal.

12:25.216 --> 12:26.332
Somebody who golfs.

12:27.404 --> 12:28.460
Does that make sense?

12:30.186 --> 12:31.692
You're jo-- You're joking?

12:31.796 --> 12:33.240
No. Oh, uh...

12:33.272 --> 12:35.207
Right here. On your--

12:35.400 --> 12:37.102
Yeah, you just have a little.
Right there.

12:37.983 --> 12:38.999
You got it.

12:40.198 --> 12:41.594
See, that's kinda
what I'm talking about.

12:44.776 --> 12:47.812
Yeah. I just don't think
you got it.

12:48.906 --> 12:50.125
To be blunt.

12:52.611 --> 12:54.892
What I will say, though,
you coming in here?

12:55.800 --> 12:57.236
I wouldn't have expected that
out of you.

12:57.261 --> 12:58.286
That took some balls.

12:58.629 --> 12:59.749
Oh, yeah.

13:02.401 --> 13:03.661
You know, I got an idea.

13:05.277 --> 13:06.810
Yeah, I tell you
what I'm gonna do.

13:07.687 --> 13:11.234
You know we have the Bangkok
merger coming up, right?

13:12.350 --> 13:13.427
Yes.

13:14.112 --> 13:15.146
Right, so...

13:15.980 --> 13:17.227
I want you on that plane.

13:18.183 --> 13:20.618
We still got outstanding issues
with Appendix-D.

13:20.894 --> 13:23.907
You take a crack at that,
solve it. Prove me wrong.

13:26.004 --> 13:27.090
That sounds fair to me.

13:27.913 --> 13:28.915
-You'll--
-Great.

13:29.574 --> 13:30.736
I'm glad we had this talk.

13:34.613 --> 13:35.629
Boom.

13:36.694 --> 13:38.039
Oh, hello.

13:38.190 --> 13:39.866
- Hello.
- Hey, sexy. Wow.

13:39.891 --> 13:41.759
Am I disturbing anything?

13:41.784 --> 13:43.798
No, no, no, we're just
wrapping it up. Hi, baby.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.311
-My God, this dress.
-Thank you.

13:45.336 --> 13:46.391
Mmm.

13:46.903 --> 13:49.439
Uh, Linda,
this is my fiancée, Zuri.

13:49.514 --> 13:50.715
Lovely to meet you.

13:53.518 --> 13:54.782
Happy fiancée.

13:55.313 --> 13:57.794
Uh, yeah. I am. Thank you?

13:58.599 --> 14:00.490
Linda's one of
our best and brightest.

14:00.631 --> 14:01.748
Thanks for stopping in.

14:01.859 --> 14:03.084
-Nice to meet you.
-Yeah, sure.

14:03.109 --> 14:05.145
Oh, Linda, before you go.
Uh...

14:05.517 --> 14:08.692
Forgot to mention. I've received
a few complaints about you.

14:09.907 --> 14:11.432
-Complaints?
-Yes.

14:11.457 --> 14:14.223
Noxious odors,
I think was the term.

14:14.248 --> 14:17.384
Uh... Tuna fish? Does that
ring a bell? At the desk.

14:18.190 --> 14:21.377
Company policy. Just...
Lunch, it's for the break room.

14:22.100 --> 14:24.102
It's a workplace.
People are trying to focus.

14:24.241 --> 14:25.477
The odors,
they can be...

14:25.597 --> 14:26.832
-a distraction.
-Mm-hmm.

14:28.219 --> 14:29.221
You understand?

14:30.375 --> 14:31.414
Understood.

14:35.186 --> 14:37.146
- That was bad.
- Right?

14:46.605 --> 14:49.624
Don't cry. Don't cry.

14:50.301 --> 14:51.335
Don't.

14:57.910 --> 15:00.835
Linda.
You listen to me.

15:01.666 --> 15:02.916
You've got this.

15:08.980 --> 15:10.815
Because you are enough.

15:12.597 --> 15:14.126
Just the way you are.

15:19.010 --> 15:23.126
You are enough,
just the way you are.

15:28.888 --> 15:29.922
Oh, fuck me.

15:31.195 --> 15:35.022
Morning, gents!
Whoo-hee!

15:35.341 --> 15:36.375
Well...

15:37.096 --> 15:39.999
Who else is ready
and raring to fly high?

15:42.601 --> 15:44.831
I am.

15:44.856 --> 15:47.787
Mr. Preston. I was working
on Appendix-D last night.

15:48.086 --> 15:49.427
I think I may have found
a loophole

15:49.452 --> 15:51.087
that could fix
all of our problems.

15:51.569 --> 15:53.615
Love to bend your ear
once everyone's settled.

15:54.319 --> 15:55.327
What?

15:55.766 --> 15:58.203
Let's go, boys.
Cocks in the air.

15:58.497 --> 15:59.798
Relax, Linda.

16:01.011 --> 16:02.209
You work too hard.

16:17.208 --> 16:19.287
Wait till you guys see
Siam Country Golf Club.

16:19.312 --> 16:20.627
That eighteenth hole.

16:20.811 --> 16:23.463
Straight uphill. Dogleg left.
I know my boy's gonna love it.

16:23.515 --> 16:26.585
I gotta show you something...

16:27.397 --> 16:28.938
...you are gonna love.

16:29.094 --> 16:31.509
Check this out.

16:42.012 --> 16:44.109
What the hell is this?

16:46.911 --> 16:48.721
- What the fuck?
- I'm Linda Liddle.

16:50.472 --> 16:52.140
No fucking way.

16:52.190 --> 16:54.394
- I wanna be the next...
- That's her?

16:54.599 --> 16:57.335
- ...Survivor!
- Oh, my God.

16:59.219 --> 17:01.615
Shh.

17:01.786 --> 17:03.114
I love to read.

17:03.795 --> 17:06.498
But I'm crazy
about the outdoors, too!

17:10.102 --> 17:12.392
I can do bush craft
with my eyes closed.

17:16.156 --> 17:17.202
You can make fire

17:17.228 --> 17:18.262
-three different ways.
-No fucking way.

17:18.502 --> 17:20.104
And I know all three of them.

17:25.926 --> 17:27.917
I work in
Strategy and Planning,

17:27.942 --> 17:31.045
