Uh...

51:23.123 --> 51:24.177
I don't.

51:24.661 --> 51:27.034
Not even the same person who
walked into my office that day.

51:28.184 --> 51:31.577
So, would you say
you underestimated me?

51:31.601 --> 51:32.635
Yeah.

51:33.197 --> 51:35.733
I would say
I gravely underestimated you.

51:35.758 --> 51:36.923
That's exactly right.

51:37.280 --> 51:38.422
I was wrong.

51:39.201 --> 51:42.379
And I really, really
want to come back to camp.

51:42.404 --> 51:43.453
Hmm.

51:43.593 --> 51:46.005
And learn from you,
if you would have me, of course.

51:53.669 --> 51:57.245
Really? Well, I think
we could discuss that.

51:57.867 --> 51:59.435
-Okay.
-Would you like to sit down?

51:59.460 --> 52:01.282
-I would love to.
-Before you fall down.

52:05.621 --> 52:07.765
-I was just thinking, you know...
-Mm-hmm?

52:08.978 --> 52:12.053
I want to help.
As much as I can, I mean.

52:12.395 --> 52:14.531
I learned the hard way. You
make all this look really easy.

52:14.556 --> 52:16.643
But, I think
that's the best bet.

52:16.668 --> 52:17.677
Working as a team.

52:18.408 --> 52:20.877
You know?
That's a smart, smart play.

52:20.902 --> 52:21.945
That is smart.

52:21.976 --> 52:23.043
-Yes.
-Yes.

52:23.313 --> 52:26.298
Definitely smart on your part.

52:26.329 --> 52:28.665
"Linda."

52:31.314 --> 52:32.349
So, what do you think?

52:32.594 --> 52:33.629
About what?

52:34.004 --> 52:35.720
Could you overlook
some of my character flaws?

52:35.744 --> 52:37.013
Of which there are many.

52:37.037 --> 52:39.096
And...

52:41.210 --> 52:43.211
...maybe I can join you
for lunch.

52:44.787 --> 52:47.225
Mmm. I don't know.

52:47.809 --> 52:48.930
Can I trust ya?

52:50.987 --> 52:53.480
You can.

52:58.014 --> 52:59.323
There was a little more on that.

53:01.583 --> 53:02.784
Linda, please.

53:03.099 --> 53:04.735
Please. Please.

53:06.194 --> 53:08.526
I'm sorry.

53:10.606 --> 53:11.637
So, is that it?

53:13.748 --> 53:15.187
-Was that it?
-Is that your pitch?

53:18.602 --> 53:20.622
What do you want from me? Huh?

53:21.798 --> 53:22.911
Well, that depends.

53:24.886 --> 53:28.854
How above and beyond
are you willing to go for me?

53:34.924 --> 53:35.942
Hmm.

53:53.809 --> 53:56.530
Oh, I'm kidding, I'm kidding.
Just keep your shirt on.

53:56.872 --> 53:58.837
I would never do that.

54:01.096 --> 54:02.331
I'm not like you.

54:06.176 --> 54:07.793
Enough.

54:09.091 --> 54:10.626
Eat.

54:11.774 --> 54:13.476
Enjoy.

54:13.501 --> 54:15.204
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

54:15.245 --> 54:17.046
-Here's some sauce.
-Thank you. Thank you.

54:17.071 --> 54:18.729
And I will get you
some more water.

54:18.755 --> 54:20.124
Thank you.

54:20.149 --> 54:22.503
- Mr. Bossypants.
- Oh, my God.

54:23.172 --> 54:26.553
What is that?

54:26.897 --> 54:28.607
Mmm.

54:30.893 --> 54:33.677
Mmm.

54:33.702 --> 54:34.718
Fuck.

54:35.799 --> 54:37.241
Ooh, mama.

54:45.006 --> 54:47.139
Ah, what do you say
we take a walk?

54:48.594 --> 54:50.093
-Sure.
-Your leg's getting so much better.

54:50.118 --> 54:51.419
We should keep rehabbing it.

54:51.483 --> 54:52.538
Where are we going?

54:53.166 --> 54:54.195
Surprise.

54:56.484 --> 54:57.922
-You okay?
-Yeah.

55:18.813 --> 55:20.315
Okay, this spot's tough.

55:23.078 --> 55:24.735
This is the tricky bit.

55:30.098 --> 55:31.518
You got it?

55:35.042 --> 55:36.641
You got it.

55:36.666 --> 55:38.630
There we go.

55:39.381 --> 55:41.811
- Yeah.
- Fun, right?

55:43.756 --> 55:44.790
Sure.

55:55.089 --> 55:56.306
Nothing for days.

55:59.396 --> 56:00.932
That's us down there.

56:02.271 --> 56:03.365
This way.

56:11.212 --> 56:12.669
Little foraging tip.

56:14.222 --> 56:16.985
So, you never want to
eat a berry

56:18.086 --> 56:19.923
that's yellow, green, or white.

56:20.108 --> 56:22.538
But if you really wanna know
if it's poisonous or not...

56:29.798 --> 56:32.603
If there's a reaction,
like that?

56:32.682 --> 56:35.097
Yeah, yeah. Don't spread it
on your morning scone, got it.

56:35.918 --> 56:37.515
Funny.

56:37.894 --> 56:39.735
All right, now down there,

56:40.202 --> 56:42.264
you see that rock
that kinda looks like an X?

56:42.290 --> 56:43.331
Yeah.

56:43.572 --> 56:45.090
So, that part of the island,

56:45.282 --> 56:48.197
it's all thorn bushes
and poison vines.

56:48.777 --> 56:49.942
Three steps into that,

56:49.967 --> 56:52.592
and you'll be scratching
your skin off for a week, so...

56:53.769 --> 56:55.337
you don't want to
go that way, ever.

56:56.645 --> 56:57.704
Okay.

56:57.729 --> 56:58.729
Okay.

56:59.341 --> 57:00.567
All right. We should head back.

57:00.592 --> 57:01.601
Yeah.

57:02.806 --> 57:03.923
Limpy McGee.

57:08.688 --> 57:11.535
I might give, uh, my leg
a breather for a minute.

57:13.008 --> 57:14.099
Yep.

57:15.115 --> 57:16.192
Take your time.

57:18.366 --> 57:19.835
Big trek down--

57:19.860 --> 57:20.927
Oh, shit!

57:24.602 --> 57:26.705
Oh, shit! Shit, here!

57:26.729 --> 57:29.341
Here. Grab on.

57:29.879 --> 57:30.914
Grab my hand.

57:30.959 --> 57:32.817
Over here, grab on.

57:47.095 --> 57:48.118
Are you okay?

57:48.890 --> 57:49.892
Thank you.

57:50.794 --> 57:51.794
I owed you one.

57:58.808 --> 58:00.143
Look what I found.

58:00.490 --> 58:01.645
Green bananas?

58:02.003 --> 58:03.252
Not for long.

58:06.403 --> 58:08.872
Gonna give Mother Nature
a little kick start.

58:12.414 --> 58:14.828
The heat turns the starch
to sugar.

58:16.426 --> 58:17.960
Try one now.

58:26.488 --> 58:27.622
Oh, my God.

58:27.647 --> 58:29.616
-Yeah?
-Oh, it's incredible.

58:29.678 --> 58:32.149
-Mmm.
-It's unbelievable. It's like...

58:32.795 --> 58:34.557
It's crispy, it's creamy.

58:34.582 --> 58:36.300
But, this is nothing.

58:37.586 --> 58:38.753
You ever heard of pruno?

58:39.208 --> 58:40.542
Pruno? What's that?

58:40.583 --> 58:43.151
It's what people in prison
drink to get intoxicated.

58:43.176 --> 58:44.190
Mmm.

58:44.580 --> 58:45.881
Mostly fermented fruit.

58:46.789 --> 58:48.372
It's otherwise known
as "toilet wine."

58:48.397 --> 58:49.430
Toilet wine.

58:50.379 --> 58:51.863
So, what?
You want to make toilet wine?

58:52.882 --> 58:54.009
Already did.

58:55.089 --> 58:56.744
Been working on it
for a few days.

58:57.807 --> 58:58.841
Wanna get drunk?

58:59.395 --> 59:00.430
Fuck yeah.

59:00.776 --> 59:01.834
All right.

59:09.070 --> 59:10.378
It's so good.

59:10.404 --> 59:11.732
Thank you, Sweetie.

59:12.113 --> 59:13.187
Just call me sweetie?

59:14.182 --> 59:15.183
I...

59:15.679 --> 59:18.300
Yes, but...
Sorry, Sweetie's my bird.

59:18.688 --> 59:20.079
Oh, you have a bird.

59:20.610 --> 59:22.484
-Yeah, I miss her.
-Yeah, I bet.

59:22.799 --> 59:24.240
Great little bird.

59:24.467 --> 59:26.633
So, you live alone with a bird?

59:26.738 --> 59:27.872
Sorry.

59:28.296 --> 59:29.341
Sorry.

59:31.975 --> 59:33.004
I was married.

59:33.997 --> 59:35.205
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

59:35.230 --> 59:36.243
Wow.

59:37.887 --> 59:38.746
-Yes.
-Not like that.

59:38.771 --> 59:39.949
I just meant, didn't know.

59:39.974 --> 59:40.982
Thanks.

59:41.276 --> 59:42.721
Yeah, ten years.

59:44.987 --> 59:46.599
-Yeah.
-So divorced or...?

59:47.014 --> 59:48.050
No, he died.

59:49.591 --> 59:50.725
Oh, I'm sorry.

59:50.750 --> 59:53.234
No, no. Don't be.
He was not very nice.

59:54.530 --> 59:55.428
Yeah. I just...

59:55.453 --> 59:57.795
I don't think
he knew how to love.

59:58.220 --> 59:59.255
Yeah.

01:00:00.002 --> 01:00:02.171
Yeah, I know how that feels.

01:00:02.370 --> 01:00:03.419
Oh, yeah?

01:00:03.984 --> 01:00:05.004
Yeah.

01:00:06.082 --> 01:00:07.582
Yeah, my parents, uh...

01:00:08.202 --> 01:00:09.237
...were the same.

01:00:09.712 --> 01:00:11.149
Both with each other and me.

01:00:11.960 --> 01:00:13.382
Dad was a total stranger.

01:00:14.624 --> 01:00:16.725
I didn't know him. Couldn't
tell you one thing about him.

01:00:18.326 --> 01:00:19.728
Was raised by my mom.

01:00:20.988 --> 01:00:22.290
Very mean person.

01:00:23.791 --> 01:00:25.627
Uh, like, abusive.

01:00:26.180 --> 01:00:28.016
Emotionally, physically.

01:00:30.820 --> 01:00:32.789
Yeah. Her father was
a piece of shit though,

01:00:32.814 --> 01:00:35.083
so, I try not to blame her, but,

01:00:35.404 --> 01:00:38.760
it's hard to not resent her,
you know?

01:00:44.914 --> 01:00:46.730
You ever hear that saying, uh,

01:00:47.002 --> 01:00:49.282
"monsters aren't born,
they're created"?

01:00:52.615 --> 01:00:54.721
Yeah. What?
Are you calling me a monster?

01:00:55.965 --> 01:00:57.500
Oh, yeah.
You're a monster, all right.

01:00:57.880 --> 01:01:00.970
Yeah. Yeah, I am.

01:01:01.416 --> 01:01:02.582
I am.

01:01:03.297 --> 01:01:04.922
At least now we know...

01:01:06.188 --> 01:01:09.124
...it's not your fault.

01:01:15.022 --> 01:01:17.229
Did you ever think about
leaving him? Your husband?

01:01:19.933 --> 01:01:20.960
Yeah.

01:01:22.237 --> 01:01:23.370
Every night.

01:01:24.980 --> 01:01:26.078
For years.

01:01:29.419 --> 01:01:32.809
I just kept hoping
he'd change, and...

01:01:33.614 --> 01:01:36.985
...just go back to how it was
in the beginning.

01:01:38.186 --> 01:01:40.217
You know, you just,
you lie to yourself,

01:01:40.242 --> 01:01:43.141
because you don't
want to be alone.

01:01:48.857 --> 01:01:49.962
How'd he die?

01:01:53.243 --> 01:01:54.464
Car accident.

01:01:58.306 --> 01:01:59.595
He was a drinker.

01:02:02.207 --> 01:02:03.505
And, uh...

01:02:05.080 --> 01:02:07.683
...I'd always hide his keys when
he got really, really drunk.

01:02:09.964 --> 01:02:12.666
And one night...
well, that night...

01:02:13.810 --> 01:02:15.123
we had a big fight.

01:02:17.306 --> 01:02:19.545
And he did some things
he shouldn't have.

01:02:22.165 --> 01:02:23.365
Awful things.

01:02:26.194 --> 01:02:27.229
Even for him.

01:02:30.479 --> 01:02:33.398
And he had
this full head of steam.

01:02:34.297 --> 01:02:36.342
He was looking for those keys.

01:02:40.081 --> 01:02:41.661
So, I took them out of my purse.

01:02:44.073 --> 01:02:45.247
Put them on the table.

01:02:47.863 --> 01:02:48.927
Let him go.

01:02:51.392 --> 01:02:52.899
Poured him his last drink.

01:03:02.790 --> 01:03:03.962
Can't believe I told you that.

01:03:03.987 --> 01:03:05.609
It's okay.

01:03:08.084 --> 01:03:09.418
I've never told anyone that.

01:03:19.295 --> 01:03:20.296
You know what?

01:03:21.202 --> 01:03:22.908
I don't think
we should ever leave here.

01:03:25.614 --> 01:03:26.731
You know what I mean?

01:03:58.894 --> 01:04:01.540
Oh, God.

01:04:58.620 --> 01:05:01.193
Here, cover the fire!

01:05:06.325 --> 01:05:09.384
Uh, we gotta get off this beach!

01:05:15.638 --> 01:05:16.871
-Are you okay?
-Yeah.

01:05:17.066 --> 01:05:18.161
We gotta go!

01:05:20.035 --> 01:05:22.347
Come on!

01:05:25.874 --> 01:05:26.968
Oh.

01:05:28.590 --> 01:05:29.712
In here!

01:05:30.425 --> 01:05:33.086
Ready? Okay. Watch your step.

01:05:33.589 --> 01:05:35.757
It gets real low here
so, careful.

01:05:42.706 --> 01:05:44.806
Okay.
This'll be good till it passes.

01:05:47.009 --> 01:05:48.474
It's fucking freezing.

01:05:48.500 --> 01:05:50.011
Take that off. Take it off.

01:05:50.992 --> 01:05:52.049
It'll help.

01:05:54.956 --> 01:05:57.066
Okay. Okay. Okay.

01:06:08.270 --> 01:06:10.325
Here. Come here.

01:06:11.205 --> 01:06:12.754
Body heat, right?

01:06:13.181 --> 01:06:15.172
Yeah, that's smart. Okay.

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:21.285
-Okay.
-Yeah, that's better.

01:06:31.206 --> 01:06:35.290
Okay.

01:06:42.729 --> 01:06:43.816
Bradley?

01:06:49.852 --> 01:06:51.087
Bradley!

01:06:54.035 --> 01:06:55.219
Bradley?

01:06:57.465 --> 01:06:58.508
Yeah.

01:07:03.604 --> 01:07:04.706
You got up early.

01:07:06.109 --> 01:07:07.341
Yeah, uh...

01:07:08.002 --> 01:07:09.103
Couldn't sleep.

01:07:10.111 --> 01:07:12.947
I went to camp,
and, uh, it's all gone.

01:07:12.972 --> 01:07:14.618
All washed away.

01:07:14.695 --> 01:07:17.436
Probably pretty stupid of me
to build so close to shore.

01:07:17.598 --> 01:07:18.642
No, it's okay.

01:07:18.906 --> 01:07:19.934
Build a new one.

01:07:21.742 --> 01:07:22.761
Yeah.

01:07:22.786 --> 01:07:24.354
Do it on higher ground
this time, right?

01:07:24.798 --> 01:07:25.876
Yeah.

01:07:25.998 --> 01:07:27.081
And I can help.

01:07:27.382 --> 01:07:29.945
I mean, getting stronger.

01:07:31.272 --> 01:07:32.325
Could do it together.

01:07:35.215 --> 01:07:36.351
I'd like that.

01:08:10.591 --> 01:08:11.692
You know, this would be
a lot easier

01:08:11.718 --> 01:08:12.779
if I could use that knife.

01:08:14.895 --> 01:08:15.899
Yeah.

01:08:16.384 --> 01:08:18.615
But you should really
learn to do it without.

01:08:19.982 --> 01:08:22.155
Take a crack at it, solve it.

01:08:22.180 --> 01:08:23.248
Prove me wrong.

01:08:23.418 --> 01:08:24.854
Didn't you say that to me once?

01:08:25.353 --> 01:08:27.657
Ah. Very good.

01:08:31.825 --> 01:08:32.877
All right.

01:08:34.196 --> 01:08:36.731
Leg's getting a little stiff.
I'm gonna take it for a walk.

01:08:37.379 --> 01:08:38.889
I think I'm gonna try to
get to the high ridge today.

01:08:40.295 --> 01:08:42.431
That's pretty far.

01:08:42.603 --> 01:08:44.987
Watch out for those poison vines
on the south side, remember?

01:08:45.012 --> 01:08:46.014
Yup.

01:08:46.327 --> 01:08:47.327
You know what?

01:08:47.663 --> 01:08:48.711
I'll join you.

01:08:50.297 --> 01:08:51.327
Sure.

01:08:51.712 --> 01:08:53.477
Need some exercise myself.

01:08:54.602 --> 01:08:56.559
Hey, I wanted
to thank you, by the way.

01:08:56.585 --> 01:08:57.653
For?

01:08:58.081 --> 01:09:00.180
Just all the things
you've taught me out here.

01:09:00.794 --> 01:09:01.958
Just in case, you know,

01:09:02.271 --> 01:09:05.137
they find us soon,
or this comes to an end.

01:09:05.900 --> 01:09:08.895
Wanted you to know
the time here, for me,

01:09:09.150 --> 01:09:10.218
it wasn't wasted.

01:09:12.314 --> 01:09:14.083
Yeah. I feel the same way.

01:09:21.608 --> 01:09:22.609
Can I make you dinner?

01:09:23.824 --> 01:09:24.828
Tomorrow night?

01:09:26.094 --> 01:09:27.495
Get you outta the kitchen
for a change?

01:09:27.520 --> 01:09:28.463
What do you think?

01:09:28.603 --> 01:09:30.638
Well, that would be nice.

01:09:42.191 --> 01:09:44.921
Good evening, madam. Thank you
for dining with us tonight.

01:09:45.113 --> 01:09:47.134
Oh, my goodness. Look at that!

01:09:47.165 --> 01:09:49.127
For starters,
we have a mango salsa,

01:09:49.164 --> 01:09:51.833
accompanied by Marian plums,
freshly picked.

01:09:52.281 --> 01:09:53.880
And for the main course,
we have a beautiful white fish.

01:09:53.906 --> 01:09:57.370
A smoked barramundi
with a wild lemon grass garnish.

01:10:00.288 --> 01:10:02.223
W-Wonderful.

01:10:02.517 --> 01:10:03.564
Bon appétit.

01:10:04.218 --> 01:10:07.046
Uh, do you,
do you cook much at home or...?

01:10:07.071 --> 01:10:08.883
No. No. Never.

01:10:08.991 --> 01:10:13.155
We either order out
or go to dinner.

01:10:13.180 --> 01:10:15.750
Occasionally, we'll have
like a chef come and cook for us

01:10:15.775 --> 01:10:17.441
-if we wanna get fancy.
-Wow. Mmm.

01:10:17.900 --> 01:10:21.393
That's you and your fiancée,
Zuri?

01:10:22.925 --> 01:10:23.977
Zuri, yeah.

01:10:25.600 --> 01:10:26.840
You must miss her, huh?

01:10:28.289 --> 01:10:29.310
Yeah.

01:10:39.434 --> 01:10:40.448
You okay?

01:10:42.792 --> 01:10:44.727
Feeling a little, uh...

01:10:47.682 --> 01:10:49.426
...dizzy, actually.

01:10:50.484 --> 01:10:52.535
Maybe you should lay down.

01:10:52.881 --> 01:10:54.818
Yeah.

01:11:11.692 --> 01:11:14.227
What?

01:11:26.763 --> 01:11:31.627
No!

01:11:58.525 --> 01:11:59.894
Yes!

01:12:00.169 --> 01:12:01.505
Fuck you, Linda!

01:12:11.473 --> 01:12:12.606
No, no, no, no!

01:12:13.595 --> 01:12:15.223
Fuck!

01:12:54.495 --> 01:12:55.864
Aw...

01:12:56.017 --> 01:12:57.552
baby.

01:13:38.393 --> 01:13:41.052
I really was just trying
to knock you out. I wasn't...

01:13:41.883 --> 01:13:43.584
I swear to God, you know...

01:13:44.692 --> 01:13:45.984
I wasn't trying to...

01:13:46.010 --> 01:13:47.799
- Just stop.
- It was just...

01:13:47.824 --> 01:13:50.731
You don't have to keep
saying that. I-I believe you.

01:13:50.756 --> 01:13:51.771
Mmm.

01:13:59.100 --> 01:14:01.725
I tasted something
bitter, but I just...

01:14:02.978 --> 01:14:04.322
I really didn't want to think

01:14:04.347 --> 01:14:05.942
you could
do something like that.

01:14:06.754 --> 01:14:07.850
But...

01:14:09.303 --> 01:14:10.339
Anyway, you know what,

01:14:10.364 --> 01:14:12.380
it would take a hell of a lot
more berries than that to...

01:14:12.794 --> 01:14:13.894
kill a human being.

01:14:14.281 --> 01:14:15.323
Yeah.

01:14:15.704 --> 01:14:16.739
For next time.

01:14:16.763 --> 01:14:19.499
I even screwed that up.

01:14:19.799 --> 01:14:20.901
Such an idiot.

01:14:26.514 --> 01:14:27.548
It's okay.

01:14:27.997 --> 01:14:29.341
I get it.

01:14:29.504 --> 01:14:31.005
Here, here, here.

01:14:31.687 --> 01:14:33.966
Come on, let's get
your strength back, huh?

01:14:34.694 --> 01:14:35.742
Again.

01:14:36.283 --> 01:14:37.369
Okay.

01:14:39.154 --> 01:14:40.554
-There you go.
-Mmm.

01:14:40.888 --> 01:14:41.913
Yeah.

01:14:44.974 --> 01:14:48.443
Now, some things are gonna
have to change with you.

01:14:49.390 --> 01:14:51.501
-And it's not gonna be easy.
-Definitely.

01:14:51.574 --> 01:14:52.594
Yeah.

01:14:53.502 --> 01:14:55.877
I've really been thinking

01:14:56.591 --> 01:14:58.608
how I can get through to you.

01:14:59.294 --> 01:15:00.693
Do you want some?
You haven't eaten.

01:15:01.415 --> 01:15:02.783
I'm okay, thanks.

01:15:02.809 --> 01:15:04.211
-You sure?
-Yeah.

01:15:04.512 --> 01:15:06.011
Still have a queasy tummy.

01:15:06.899 --> 01:15:07.903
Right.

01:15:09.425 --> 01:15:10.559
-I know how hard...
-So stupid.

01:15:10.584 --> 01:15:12.038
...this all must be for you.

01:15:13.288 --> 01:15:14.923
Not being in control.

01:15:15.597 --> 01:15:16.825
-Ahh.
-You're not used to...

01:15:17.692 --> 01:15:19.846
being in this, shall we say,

01:15:20.874 --> 01:15:23.869
...submissive position.

01:15:24.687 --> 01:15:27.597
I mean, it's natural for you not
to be able to take orders from me.

01:15:27.628 --> 01:15:30.843
To have to depend on me
for your survival.

01:15:31.118 --> 01:15:32.286
You know?

01:15:33.414 --> 01:15:34.488
It's just natural.

01:15:34.935 --> 01:15:36.708
You're a slave to your biology.

01:15:36.897 --> 01:15:38.524
Oh!

01:15:40.009 --> 01:15:41.843
Feeling kinda funny, huh?

01:15:42.598 --> 01:15:44.420
Can't move?

01:15:44.792 --> 01:15:48.387
That's the neurotoxins
from this blue-ringed octopus.

01:15:49.684 --> 01:15:53.146
Blocks the transmission
of nerve impulses.

01:15:54.882 --> 01:15:56.406
Caught it about a week ago.

01:15:57.385 --> 01:16:00.461
Was really hoping I wouldn't
have to use it, but...

01:16:01.183 --> 01:16:02.384
...held on to it.

01:16:03.712 --> 01:16:04.912
Just in case.

01:16:08.730 --> 01:16:11.666
Now, you did a great job
with that raft. I gotta say.

01:16:11.900 --> 01:16:13.341
You really are a quick study.

01:16:14.570 --> 01:16:16.920
But if you really wanted it
to hold...

01:16:18.572 --> 01:16:21.737
...you should have used
double floor lashing.

01:16:23.231 --> 01:16:24.811
But, of course,
I never taught you that one.

01:16:25.406 --> 01:16:26.478
Shoot.

01:16:29.224 --> 01:16:32.760
Now, I just want to put
your mind at ease, okay?

01:16:33.708 --> 01:16:36.878
The toxins from the
Hapalochlaena lunulata

01:16:37.491 --> 01:16:38.551
aren't gonna kill you.

01:16:39.815 --> 01:16:41.825
And I promise
they will wear off.

01:16:42.504 --> 01:16:44.618
But right now, you won't be able
to move or feel anything.

01:16:45.599 --> 01:16:47.221
And trust me...

01:16:47.616 --> 01:16:49.167
...I think you want it that way.

01:16:49.998 --> 01:16:51.098
Ooh.

01:17:02.215 --> 01:17:03.295
Where was I?

01:17:04.293 --> 01:17:09.046
So, when I was a little girl,
we had this dog.

01:17:10.698 --> 01:17:13.834
Very, very naughty dog.
So disobedient.

01:17:13.859 --> 01:17:16.738
Always running away.

01:17:19.805 --> 01:17:23.404
And my dad said,
"It's not his fault.

01:17:23.430 --> 01:17:26.088
He just..."

01:17:28.596 --> 01:17:31.230
"...needs to be fixed."

01:17:36.982 --> 01:17:37.991
Now...

01:17:39.594 --> 01:17:42.103
it's actually quite a simple...

01:17:43.196 --> 01:17:44.518
...medical procedure.

01:17:44.826 --> 01:17:48.229
They used to do it
all the time to Egyptian slaves.

01:17:48.789 --> 01:17:51.506
Made them more, um, obedient.

01:17:52.419 --> 01:17:53.904
Compliant.

01:17:56.910 --> 01:17:57.916
Okay.

01:18:00.595 --> 01:18:01.930
No help is coming.

01:18:03.785 --> 01:18:05.919
This is the way things are now.

01:18:06.208 --> 01:18:08.143
And you need
to just accept that.

01:18:09.903 --> 01:18:11.300
You are stuck.

01:18:12.213 --> 01:18:13.415
No power.

01:18:13.801 --> 01:18:15.824
Low end of the totem pole.

01:18:17.064 --> 01:18:18.999
With some asshole boss.

01:18:19.967 --> 01:18:21.302
Just like I was.

01:18:22.302 --> 01:18:23.707
Although, I'm betting...

01:18:23.992 --> 01:18:27.398
I am a much nicer boss
than you ever would have been.

01:18:29.591 --> 01:18:32.527
Except for maybe this part.

01:18:35.430 --> 01:18:36.513
Ready?

01:18:43.618 --> 01:18:45.027
Okay.

01:18:45.052 --> 01:18:46.377
Now, now, don't be a baby.

01:18:46.402 --> 01:18:47.829
You're not gonna miss
this stuff.

01:18:56.881 --> 01:18:58.347
Ooh!

01:19:00.539 --> 01:19:02.467
We got a bleeder here.

01:19:02.492 --> 01:19:04.737
A lot of blood.

01:19:04.762 --> 01:19:06.415
Wow.

01:19:10.435 --> 01:19:11.504
Oh.

01:19:18.285 --> 01:19:20.269
It's okay. It's just a rat.

01:19:25.699 --> 01:19:27.586
Next time it won't be a rat.

01:19:29.990 --> 01:19:33.624
So, don't ever mistake
my kindness for weakness.

01:19:48.469 --> 01:19:49.571
Hey, there!

01:19:50.965 --> 01:19:52.008
How goes it?

01:19:55.796 --> 01:19:57.897
Barely talked in two days,
you Gloomy Gus.

01:20:02.303 --> 01:20:04.117
Would it kill you
to give me a little smile?

01:20:12.599 --> 01:20:14.624
Mmm. There it is.

01:20:16.203 --> 01:20:17.772
Tell you what I'm gonna do
to cheer you up.

01:20:18.738 --> 01:20:20.184
I'm gonna go find...

01:20:21.302 --> 01:20:24.619
the juiciest, most beautiful
fruits on this whole island

01:20:24.644 --> 01:20:25.813
and make you a little treat.

01:20:31.613 --> 01:20:33.423
Such a sourpuss.

01:20:33.501 --> 01:20:36.470
Make him a little fire,
and he's gonna come around.

01:20:49.803 --> 01:20:52.033
Hello? Hello?

01:20:52.058 --> 01:20:53.081
Shit.

01:20:55.616 --> 01:20:58.020
Linda! It's me.

01:20:58.045 --> 01:21:00.893
Shit, shit,
shit, shit, shit, shit...

01:21:00.918 --> 01:21:04.721
Oh, my God! We found her!
I did it. I can't believe it.

01:21:04.893 --> 01:21:05.918
Hey.

01:21:07.389 --> 01:21:08.724
-Hey.
-No, no, no.

01:21:09.991 --> 01:21:11.684
Come here!

01:21:11.709 --> 01:21:12.749
Oh, my God.

01:21:12.879 --> 01:21:14.848
Hi. Hello.

01:21:16.410 --> 01:21:18.446
Is he alive? Is he here?

01:21:18.471 --> 01:21:19.442
How on earth?

01:21:19.467 --> 01:21:21.622
Bradley, is he-- is he here?

01:21:21.647 --> 01:21:22.878
-Yes.
-He is?

01:21:22.903 --> 01:21:24.286
-Yes, he's here.
-Oh, my God.

01:21:24.312 --> 01:21:26.505
-He is here.
-He's alive!

01:21:27.200 --> 01:21:29.104
Even when they called off
the search in this area,

01:21:29.136 --> 01:21:30.312
I never gave up.

01:21:30.336 --> 01:21:32.884
-I couldn't give up.
-That's amazing.

01:21:32.909 --> 01:21:35.220
I hired my own boat,
I did my own search.

01:21:35.488 --> 01:21:37.448
Is he okay? Is he hurt? Is he...

01:21:37.473 --> 01:21:38.874
He's fine.

01:21:39.486 --> 01:21:42.285
-He's so good. He's great.
-Great.

01:21:42.310 --> 01:21:44.252
I can't believe
this is happening.

01:21:44.277 --> 01:21:46.191
I know.

01:21:46.216 --> 01:21:48.118
Please, can you take me to him?
Right now?

01:21:48.143 --> 01:21:50.112
-I need to see him. Please.
-He's, um...

01:21:50.184 --> 01:21:51.218
Is he just down here?

01:21:51.243 --> 01:21:52.523
-Yes, he's out here.
-Yeah? He is?

01:21:52.548 --> 01:21:53.475
No, no, no.

01:21:53.500 --> 01:21:54.735
-He's not over there.
-Bradley, I'm here!

01:21:54.760 --> 01:21:56.794
-Um--
-Bradley, where are you?

01:21:56.898 --> 01:21:58.098
Should we follow you?

01:21:59.220 --> 01:22:00.230
This way?

01:22:03.271 --> 01:22:04.413
Should we follow you?

01:22:04.438 --> 01:22:05.512
Uh...

01:22:06.513 --> 01:22:09.509
-I just need to get my stuff.
-You're not gonna need this.

01:22:09.535 --> 01:22:10.563
Ow.

01:22:10.588 --> 01:22:13.308
-Sorry. Sorry, I just...
-You like mango, right?

01:22:13.881 --> 01:22:15.034
Yeah, I worked really hard.

01:22:15.059 --> 01:22:16.539
We got lots of food on the boat.

01:22:18.878 --> 01:22:19.906
Oh, yum.

01:22:20.800 --> 01:22:21.907
Yum, yum, yum.

01:22:22.409 --> 01:22:23.506
Lead the way.

01:22:24.325 --> 01:22:27.252
So, is it just the two of you?

01:22:28.095 --> 01:22:30.522
Or is there a whole search party
waiting for us?

01:22:30.556 --> 01:22:31.580
Just us.

01:22:32.512 --> 01:22:35.895
But there will be many people
happy to hear you two are alive.

01:22:36.017 --> 01:22:37.088
Once I radio back.

01:22:37.120 --> 01:22:39.001
You'll be back in your own bed
in no time.

01:22:40.020 --> 01:22:41.908
There's a shortcut
just ahead here.

01:22:52.286 --> 01:22:54.976
I bet you can't wait
to return to your life.

01:22:55.080 --> 01:22:58.472
Your job, your family,
your friends.

01:23:23.084 --> 01:23:25.269
Uh, shoelace.

01:23:26.279 --> 01:23:27.322
Okay.

01:23:27.910 --> 01:23:30.331
- Just follow the trail.
- Yeah.

01:23:30.550 --> 01:23:31.919
I'm right behind you.

01:23:53.707 --> 01:23:55.852
Zuri! Zuri! Zuri! Come on!

01:23:55.877 --> 01:23:58.096
Grab my hand. Hey. Come on!

01:23:58.587 --> 01:24:01.097
I got you. I got you.
You can do it. You can do it.

01:24:01.122 --> 01:24:02.835
Help me! Help me!

01:24:02.860 --> 01:24:04.863
Come on. Come on.

01:24:04.888 --> 01:24:05.888
I got you!

01:24:05.980 --> 01:24:07.273
- Zuri! Come on.
- Linda, help us!

01:24:07.298 --> 01:24:09.134
I got you. You can do it.
You can do it.

01:24:09.384 --> 01:24:10.985
I got you. You can do it.

01:24:11.010 --> 01:24:12.645
Man:

01:24:12.670 --> 01:24:13.938
Help me!

01:24:13.988 --> 01:24:15.455
-Linda!
-Linda!

01:24:15.678 --> 01:24:17.114
Help us!

01:24:17.195 --> 01:24:19.954
Linda!

01:24:31.091 --> 01:24:32.226
Dinner.

01:24:33.787 --> 01:24:34.944
Yep.

01:25:26.687 --> 01:25:28.950
Saw some fresh boar tracks
earlier today.

01:25:30.284 --> 01:25:31.965
We haven't had protein
in awhile.

01:25:33.587 --> 01:25:35.438
Maybe when it clears up
we should go hunting.

01:25:39.306 --> 01:25:40.648
I'm taking a sick day.

01:25:44.058 --> 01:25:45.325
Can't do it on my own.

01:26:28.521 --> 01:26:30.208
Linda!

01:27:36.684 --> 01:27:38.226
Linda.

01:27:39.721 --> 01:27:41.689
Linda!

01:27:43.170 --> 01:27:45.585
You tried to kill me.

01:27:45.725 --> 01:27:47.438
-No.
-Why?

01:27:48.089 --> 01:27:49.329
Why?

01:27:49.963 --> 01:27:51.772
Why'd you do it?

01:27:53.187 --> 01:27:57.103
Why?

01:27:57.197 --> 01:27:58.996
Why'd you have to come?

01:27:59.219 --> 01:28:00.615
I'm gonna tell Bradley
everything.

01:28:00.640 --> 01:28:01.542
No.

01:28:01.566 --> 01:28:02.793
-You're a murderer.
-No.

01:28:02.818 --> 01:28:03.899
You are!

01:28:53.127 --> 01:28:55.807
Fuck!

01:30:08.607 --> 01:30:09.663
Where you been?

01:30:12.339 --> 01:30:13.406
Nowhere.

01:30:15.695 --> 01:30:17.564
Take another sick day?

01:30:22.575 --> 01:30:23.744
What is it?

01:30:27.200 --> 01:30:28.302
You know what's happening.

01:30:29.642 --> 01:30:31.109
No, I don't actually.

01:30:31.135 --> 01:30:32.136
You don't?

01:30:32.979 --> 01:30:34.902
I don't. I don't actually.

01:30:35.309 --> 01:30:36.477
Did you kill her?

01:30:40.915 --> 01:30:41.985
Who?

01:30:51.312 --> 01:30:52.614
She slipped.

01:30:53.793 --> 01:30:56.749
I was trying to bring her to you
and she got ahead--

01:30:56.774 --> 01:30:57.974
Why didn't you tell me?

01:30:57.998 --> 01:30:59.099
Because I knew
how it would look...

01:30:59.125 --> 01:31:00.513
Why wouldn't you tell me
she came here?

01:31:00.538 --> 01:31:01.519
...and I knew you wouldn't
believe me!

01:31:02.075 --> 01:31:03.477
You wouldn't believe me!

01:31:03.724 --> 01:31:06.112
You're right, I don't.

01:31:06.701 --> 01:31:07.767
I don't believe you.

01:31:11.979 --> 01:31:13.803
It was an accident.

01:31:14.294 --> 01:31:16.497
I swear to you.

01:31:17.404 --> 01:31:19.509
Just like your husband's
death was an accident?

01:32:54.934 --> 01:32:58.469
You motherfucker!

01:33:11.460 --> 01:33:12.695
Oh, fuck!

01:33:12.818 --> 01:33:13.925
What the fuck?

01:34:01.280 --> 01:34:03.549
Fuck you, Bradley!

01:34:23.417 --> 01:34:24.682
Oh!

01:34:29.436 --> 01:34:30.681
Where'd you go?

01:35:19.900 --> 01:35:22.975
Hey. Hey!

01:35:25.165 --> 01:35:26.166
Hey!

01:35:28.608 --> 01:35:31.579
Hey!

01:35:40.887 --> 01:35:42.380
Hey!

01:36:08.987 --> 01:36:12.407
What the fuck?

01:36:17.491 --> 01:36:19.853
Oh, is there anything
more civilized

01:36:19.878 --> 01:36:21.513
than refrigeration?

01:36:23.574 --> 01:36:25.198
There's a frozen
Massaman curry in there

01:36:25.223 --> 01:36:26.330
that's to die for.

01:36:30.278 --> 01:36:31.846
You looking for a knife?

01:36:32.585 --> 01:36:35.825
Yeah. I got rid of all
of those.

01:36:36.696 --> 01:36:38.082
Except for one.

01:36:39.892 --> 01:36:41.054
Hey, pal.

01:36:42.395 --> 01:36:44.817
So tell me, Bradley,

01:36:45.091 --> 01:36:48.425
how does a knife
just wash up on shore?

01:36:49.796 --> 01:36:51.802
You really crack me up
sometimes.

01:36:55.501 --> 01:36:57.611
Where you going? Where
you going? Where you going?

01:36:58.578 --> 01:36:59.584
Oh, there you are.

01:37:00.954 --> 01:37:02.403
Nice place, huh?

01:37:03.190 --> 01:37:05.558
Owner is some
Wall Street billionaire.

01:37:06.493 --> 01:37:08.818
First thing I did
was turn off the security.

01:37:09.189 --> 01:37:11.625
Guy didn't even notice.

01:37:12.705 --> 01:37:15.552
Bradley, I have a confession to
make and I feel sick about it.

01:37:17.184 --> 01:37:18.902
Sorry to tell you this, but...

01:37:19.912 --> 01:37:21.949
we could've been rescued
some time ago.

01:37:24.858 --> 01:37:26.871
But I wasn't
ready to leave yet.

01:37:29.877 --> 01:37:32.012
I just needed
a little more time.

01:37:55.695 --> 01:37:57.497
After the caretakers left...

01:37:58.706 --> 01:38:00.124
I broke in.

01:38:01.474 --> 01:38:03.142
It was easy.

01:38:33.379 --> 01:38:36.835
And then you and me,
we were alone again.

01:38:38.650 --> 01:38:41.087
It was... perfect.

01:38:41.900 --> 01:38:43.340
What the fuck.

01:38:44.098 --> 01:38:46.603
Just me and my new Sweetie.

01:38:48.488 --> 01:38:51.979
Well, for a little while.

01:38:53.612 --> 01:38:55.416
Things just kept happening.

01:38:57.011 --> 01:38:58.528
It's not like I planned it.

01:39:00.480 --> 01:39:01.747
I swear to you.

01:39:02.909 --> 01:39:04.306
I didn't want any of this.

01:39:04.436 --> 01:39:05.507
Linda!

01:39:06.892 --> 01:39:10.289
Come on, girl!
You can do it, I got you!

01:39:10.569 --> 01:39:13.763
Zuri! Zuri! I got you!
You can do it! You can do it!

01:39:14.814 --> 01:39:16.895
I got you!

01:39:16.920 --> 01:39:21.080
Linda!

01:39:32.619 --> 01:39:33.620
Bradley?

01:39:35.416 --> 01:39:40.410
Don't you wonder why we were
the only ones who made it?

01:39:44.960 --> 01:39:48.219
Maybe it was written
in the stars.

01:40:14.801 --> 01:40:16.905
I'm sorry it had to be this way.

01:40:18.411 --> 01:40:20.246
Because it could've been
so good.

01:40:20.271 --> 01:40:22.600
Wait, wait, please,
please, please. You were right.

01:40:22.677 --> 01:40:24.049
You were right.
You were right, okay?

01:40:24.074 --> 01:40:26.270
I was-- I was a piece of shit.

01:40:26.295 --> 01:40:28.463
-I was a terrible person.
-Uh-huh.

01:40:28.488 --> 01:40:29.922
I was, uh...

01:40:29.947 --> 01:40:33.023
I was a monster.
I was.

01:40:33.886 --> 01:40:38.496
I was a monster!

01:40:40.580 --> 01:40:44.630
The way I treated everyone.

01:40:45.885 --> 01:40:48.722
I'm so broken.

01:40:49.662 --> 01:40:51.201
You broke me.

01:40:55.000 --> 01:40:56.368
I've changed.

01:40:57.997 --> 01:41:03.800
Really, I have. I can feel it.

01:41:04.024 --> 01:41:07.393
Because of you. Because I... I--

01:41:08.822 --> 01:41:09.856
Linda...

01:41:12.298 --> 01:41:13.930
I think you're
the most incredible person

01:41:13.955 --> 01:41:14.978
I've ever known.

01:41:17.816 --> 01:41:19.051
You took care of me.

01:41:20.201 --> 01:41:21.312
I tried.

01:41:21.687 --> 01:41:24.345
You did.
And you taught me things.

01:41:26.520 --> 01:41:29.036
No one's ever taken the time
to teach me anything.

01:41:37.490 --> 01:41:38.682
You saved me.

01:41:42.902 --> 01:41:46.103
I felt love from you in a way
that I've never...

01:41:46.580 --> 01:41:48.133
felt from anyone.

01:41:54.861 --> 01:41:56.615
I think we can make this work.

01:41:58.378 --> 01:42:00.371
-What?
-Here.

01:42:03.503 --> 01:42:04.613
No, you don't.

01:42:05.091 --> 01:42:07.835
Yeah. You were right.
We can stay.

01:42:09.088 --> 01:42:11.312
You proved it yourself
we can survive.

01:42:12.184 --> 01:42:13.705
We have everything we need.

01:42:14.961 --> 01:42:15.994
Yeah.

01:42:17.177 --> 01:42:18.846
That's what I've been saying.

01:42:18.871 --> 01:42:19.872
I know.

01:42:21.094 --> 01:42:23.340
There's nothing for us
back there.

01:42:25.392 --> 01:42:27.426
I want to be happy.

01:42:27.451 --> 01:42:29.044
With you, here.

01:42:30.490 --> 01:42:32.291
Just us, you and me.

01:42:37.985 --> 01:42:39.100
I see it now.

01:42:43.617 --> 01:42:45.099
Actually happy?

01:42:46.104 --> 01:42:47.267
Not some bullshit?

01:42:47.292 --> 01:42:49.031
Not some fucking bullshit.

01:42:50.705 --> 01:42:52.318
You want to go back
to that life?

01:42:52.343 --> 01:42:53.611
No fucking way.

01:42:53.887 --> 01:42:55.807
What would we go back to?

01:42:55.890 --> 01:42:57.514
-Nothing.
-Nothing.

01:42:58.997 --> 01:43:04.218
We stay here, you and me,
forever.

01:43:07.381 --> 01:43:08.582
That sounds...

01:43:10.175 --> 01:43:11.611
...like a fairy tale.

01:43:18.604 --> 01:43:20.206
I love you so much.

01:43:24.910 --> 01:43:26.592
Why did you make it so hard?

01:43:26.913 --> 01:43:28.059
I'm a fucking idiot.

01:43:31.484 --> 01:43:33.453
Oh, sorry I gouged your eye out.

01:43:35.755 --> 01:43:37.057
Sorry I stabbed you.

01:43:40.414 --> 01:43:42.615
You did! Oh, you did.

01:43:44.388 --> 01:43:45.477
God, I love you.

01:43:45.574 --> 01:43:46.950
I love you.

01:43:59.819 --> 01:44:01.618
No!

01:44:07.770 --> 01:44:09.687
Bye, you crazy bitch
from Accounting.

01:44:09.712 --> 01:44:12.522
No.
No!

01:44:18.572 --> 01:44:21.070
Ow! Fuck!

01:44:27.580 --> 01:44:29.181
Strategy and Planning.

01:44:36.395 --> 01:44:37.499
Boom.

01:44:41.874 --> 01:44:43.254
This is Polly Perera, here

01:44:43.279 --> 01:44:46.312
at the 19th Annual
Celebrity Golf Invitational.

01:44:46.384 --> 01:44:50.008
And we're here with everyone's
favorite real-life survivor...

01:44:50.095 --> 01:44:51.997
Linda Liddle.

01:44:52.022 --> 01:44:53.323
You're looking
pretty good out here.

01:44:53.348 --> 01:44:56.275
Oh, thanks, Polly.
It's a game I've grown to love.

01:44:56.998 --> 01:44:59.333
Linda, it's been almost a year

01:44:59.358 --> 01:45:01.078
since the world
fell in love with you,

01:45:01.103 --> 01:45:03.686
when you were found
alone at sea on a raft,

01:45:03.711 --> 01:45:07.411
the only survivor of a terrible
plane crash. How did you do it?

01:45:09.135 --> 01:45:11.169
Well, it wasn't easy.

01:45:11.194 --> 01:45:15.299
But the memory
of my lost colleagues is what...

01:45:16.489 --> 01:45:19.239
...drove me forward
and kept me hanging in there.

01:45:20.801 --> 01:45:23.725
Your incredible best-seller
is being turned into a movie.

01:45:24.579 --> 01:45:26.296
-What's next for you?
-I can't even believe it.

01:45:27.939 --> 01:45:29.679
So next, uh...

01:45:29.704 --> 01:45:31.797
Well, I'm writing
a self-help book.

01:45:32.786 --> 01:45:34.414
Because I want people to know...

01:45:36.314 --> 01:45:37.689
...no help is coming.

01:45:38.686 --> 01:45:40.608
So you better start
saving yourself.

